Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of mobile autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach of generating intelligent schedules for resource-performance trade-offs involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) such as optimization and multi-objective verification. The use of schedules also involves system design and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions correct-by-construction scheduling, which is a software engineering concept (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the framework for generating schedules, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
